==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hindleys screw
<hw>Hind"ley"s screw`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Mech.)</fld> <def>A screw
cut on a solid whose sides are arcs of the periphery of a wheel into the
teeth of which the screw is intended to work. It is named from the
person who first used the form.</def></p>

<p><ent>Hindu</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Hindoo</ent>⟦br⟧
